		<div id="post_message_1246103">
                  
                  The primary feeling, I got, when I first read the letter was: he is talking big about what they have done so far (which did not change a lot for me, I still crash regular and have some major glitches when playing the game which includes quests, graphics, performance and overall game play) and he is promising things which don’t matter and in addition everything complex they are not going to deliver anyway.<br />
<br />
When I wrote my post on the SOE forum, I checked back with the letter, for the different things I feel important about and I found that I could read something into it, that they may be in scope of the “Vision”. But I still believe everything which takes a major effort will not going to happen.<br />
<br />
Getting raid into the game took them how long? I think some of my expectations are quite big compared to the step of implementing raids.<br />
<br />
At the other hand I’m pleased that the development team is spending time on the classes which is high on my issue list. In the end, I have very mixed feelings about what’s going on at the moment regarding SOE and Vanguard.
                  
