</div>
<br />
Honestly, good lore is the key to feeling a part of the game.<br />
<br />
A long long time ago, i bought an XPac called &quot;Scars of Velious&quot;.<br />
All i knew about it, was Dragons/Dwarfs/Giants + Frost<br />
<br />
<br />
So i arrived at &quot;low 40s&quot; by a druid friend that TPed me to Great Divide.<br />
3 mins later i was running for my life (in SoW we trust) since i had agroed a wyrm.<br />
Needless to say, i ran for a long time, made a huge train, and zoned someplace i didnt know (Western Wastes).<br />
<br />
He took me to an awesome looking giant town (where i was praying inviz not to drop).<br />
Then across a huge forest with panthers, then to Cobalt Scar (for the tooth).<br />
Ported me back to Great Divide, showed me where Velketors is and left me there.<br />
<br />
Slowly i discovered the world... <br />
A town of smelly dwarfs (with great velium loots) at war with Giants.<br />
A crazed giant sorcerer with all his crystal statues pets (velketor).<br />
An awesome looking giant town where i wasnt KoS (RZ diety warrior)<br />
A huge forest with some really hostile stuff and a gay portal camping dragon.<br />
A lost tower of some sorcerer with traps &amp; 6 7 floors.<br />
A huge wasteland filled with VERY hostile dragons (fuck Mraaka).<br />
An enormous necropolis guarded by a badass dragon.<br />
Temple of Veeshan, the zone dedicated to the dragon god.<br />
Several expeditions to go farm armor with the guild.<br />
Betraying giants because some of their loots were incredible.<br />
Killing the &quot;Dragon Dwarf Giant&quot; kings ! (that was a rush).<br />
Joining a &quot;Ring 10 War&quot; just for the fun.<br />
Seeing a 30 man guild decimated in 20 seconds by an &quot;Molten Metal Avatar&quot;<br />
<br />
Rumors about a &quot;Tomb&quot; with some absolutely monstrous mob.<br />
<br />
<br />
I could go on for hours and hours about velious....<br />
The adventure started at 37 when you entered The Great Divide.<br />
It ended after many months, in Sleepers Tomb.<br />
<br />
The rush, pride i felt when i got my ST Key....<br />
Beeing trusted/rewarded, and asset, with such a precious/rare key.<br />
<br />
Velious felt like a &quot;World&quot; not 2+1 continents with 30 independant zones each VG is.<br />
<br />
<br />
I still play hardcore (40+h per week), but i'm a child of &quot;Conan&quot; and &quot;AD&amp;D&quot;.<br />
Which means that backround/history/feeling is a lot more important than<br />
PvPing some tauren drood in a horribly fucked up instanced anathema they call WoW.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
