                  Good point about people not reading quest text anymore. You know why? Because you don't have to. I played the whole Ultima series as a kid as well. I'll never forget getting Ultima III Exodus and how cool the box was for my Commodore64. <img src="images/smilies/biggrin.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Big Grin" class="inlineimg" />   <br />
<br />
  You know what that game made you do? Read the text, all of it! Then you had to try different sayings to get the NPC to go on with more story. My 1st MMO was EQ and it did the same thing. I'm not entirely sure that there aren't games out there with good stories anymore, I just think they've made it too easy to click, click, click... &quot;ok, what do i have to do now?&quot;<br />
