		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1249550">
                  
                  Kunark was, by far, the best EQ expansion, but I seem to remember spending more time in Velious than once it came out. But I honestly liked Luclin the most, and took almost a full year out from my wiz to raise a Vah Shir BL.<br />
<br />
It was all down hill from there though - mainly because I am not at heart a heavy raider: once or twice a month is my raiding speed, and I enjoy soloing most. I'm not adverse to groups, I just prefer solo most of the time. PoP was the end of solo play, period, for EQ. It went, for me, from mostly solo and a fair amount of grouping, to grouping all the time with a lot of raiding thrown in. I just found myself enjoying it less and less, and when EQ2 beta came along, I quietly faded away.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
